 which inclusion and recognition are forms of harm rather than remedies to it. In calling for trans/queer organizing and worldmaking beyond these forms, Stanley points to abolitionist ways of life that might offer livable futures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAfrican American transgender peoplexViolence againstzUnited States. 0aGender-nonconforming peoplexMinoritiesxViolence againstzUnited States. 0aGender-nonconforming peoplexViolence againstzUnited States. 0aHomophobiaxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aMinority transgender womenxViolence againstzUnited States. 0aTransgender peoplexMinoritiesxViolence againstzUnited States. 0aTransgender peoplexViolence againstzUnited States. 0aTransphobiaxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Transgender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147802152040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478021520423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478021520/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DSLb2021